The recent inflation report showed little enthusiasm for households affected by rising inflation and marginal wage increases, as the tightening becomes worse before it improves.
She added that monetary policy cannot 'prevent' the loss of income over the next few years, but she added that wages will 'recover significantly' at the end of their three-year forecast.
The economy is also strengthened by rising demand for British goods, owing to the weak pound, which will compensate for part of lower consumer spending.
