There is still much to be done by March.
"It is actually a beautiful hotel," says Thomas Scherer in conversation with our newspaper.
Everything is to be renewed in the Black Forest style.
The rooms are equipped with large walk-in showers, the entrance area is redesigned and new windows are installed.
Everything should later become "pretty close to the citizen", as Thomas Scherer puts it.
'We want to make a jewel on it '.
Swimming pool, spa and meeting room are all equipped.
You don ’ t want to position yourself at the high level of the hotels in Lauterbad, but you don ’ t want to be at an upscale city level, Scherer points out.
The Waldhotel Luise, with its 60 rooms, wants to be wide, Scherer explains.
Both individual holidaymakers, groups or businessmen should feel at home in the hotel.
He has already held talks with OB Julian Osswald and tourism director Michael Krause, according to Scherer.
The ideas of the city are identical to those of the hotel group.
'We are on the same line '.
When asked about the level of investment, Thomas Scherer does not want to be precise.
Almost less than a million euros, he expects.
The outdoor installations are also brought to the fore, which is already clearly visible.
A large terrace is created in a courtyard which will be accessible from the restaurant, which is open to the public.
