The Larsen-C-Schelfeis is is located south of South America almost at the tip of the Antarctic Peninsula.
North of this horseshoe, the balance of waxes and breakdowns a few years ago was disturbed.
A complete scoop had broken up there, writes AWI Research writer Daniela Jansen.
